ISLAMABAD -- Rahoton U.N. ya ce fiye da 6,000 na 'yan ta'addan Pakistan suna tsarkake a Afghanistan, mafi yawan daga cikin su suna da alaka da kungiyar ta'addanci ta Pakistan ta haramta da take da alaka da yin harbe-harbe ga jami'an soja da kuma jama'a na Pakistan.
Rahoton da aka fitar wannan mako ya ce, wani kungiya da aka sani da Tehreek-e-Taliban (TTP) ya hada kai da kungiyar Islamic State da ke Afghanistan.
Wasu daga manyan jama'a na TTP sun koma kungiyar IS mai gidansa a yankin Arewacin Afghanistan.
Gwamnatin Afghan ba ta amsa ranar Lahadi zuwa bukatar AP don magana ba.
Rahoton ya ce IS a Afaganistan, wanda aka sani da IS a yankin Khorasan, ya samu rauni mai tsanani daga kungiyoyin tsaro na Afaganistan da kuma kungiyoyin Amurka da NATO, har ma da lokutan da taliban Afagan suka yi.
Rahoton an gina ne ta hanyar kungiyar U.N. ta binciken bayanai da kuma kula da yaki da laifuka, wanda ke bincika kungiyoyin ta'addanci a duniya.
Rahoton ya kiyasta yawan jama'ar IS a Afghanistan a 2,200, kuma yayin da shugabancinsa ya yi yawa, IS har yanzu yana daga cikin shugabanninsa wani mutumin Syria Abu Said Mohammad al-Khorasani.
Rahoton ma ya ce, jami'ar kula da yanayin ya samu labarin cewa biyu daga cikin masu ruwa da tsaki na kungiyar IS, Abu Qutaibah da Abu Hajar al-Iraqi, sun zo Afghanistan daga yammacin Turai da makwabtaka.
Duk da ci gaba da koma gida, (Jamhuriyar Musulunci) yana da ikon yin muhimman harin a cikin yankunan daban-daban na kasar, ciki har da Kabul.
Yana nufin kuma ya kokarin janyo wa 'yan Taliban da suka yi musu baya ga yarjejeniyar da Amurka ta yi da Taliban a watan Fabrairu, kamar yadda rahoton ya ce.
An yi wannan yarjejeniya don barin Amurka ta yi shekaru 19 a Afghanistan, kuma an yi kira ga Taliban su tabbatar da cewa babban yankin su ba zai yi amfani da shi ba wajen yin aikace-aikacen ta'addanci.
Aikace-aikacen ya kuma ake fatan zai tabbatar da halartar Taliban gaba daya a cikin yakin da za a yi da IS.
Tsarin biyu da mafi muhimmanci na yarjejeniyar yana buƙatar tattaunawa tsakanin Taliban da jagorancin siyasa na Kabul.
Ranar Asabar da ta gabata, Ma'aikatar Shiga ta Amurka ta fitar da wata sanarwa cewa tawagar zaman lafiya ta ta, Zalmay Khalilzad, ta sake yin tafiya a yankin don fara wannan tattaunawa da aka sake kara lokuta, inda dukkan biyu suka yi kangarar baki game da wani shirin sakin jama'a.
Aikace-aikacen US ta goyon bayan ya kira ga gwamnatin Afghan ta saki 5,000 'yan Taliban da kuma Taliban su saki 1,000 ma'aikata da jami'an tsaro a matsayin wani abu da ake kira alfahari a gaban tattaunawa.
Yanzu haka gwamnatin ta ki sakin 'yan Taliban da dama da take kira masu laifi muhimmanci, kuma ta bayar da zaɓuɓɓuka don sakin su.
Taliban sun ki karba.
Aikin gwamnatin Amurka ya ce, "Dangantakar jam'iyyun sun fi kusa da fara tattaunawa tsakanin Afghan, wanda shine matakin gaba wajen kammala yakin shekaru 40 da Afghanistan ta sha."
Duk da ci gaba mai yawa ya samu a kan dawo da marayu, wannan batu ya bukaci karin aiki don a cimma matsayin gaba daya.
Spokan siyasa na Taliban a ranar Litinin da ta gabata ya ce suna shirye su yi magana da jagororin siyasa na Kabul bayan bikin musulunci na Eid al-Adha a karshen wannan watan, in an gama da sakin mutane.
Pakistan ta sha wahala sosai saboda jama'a masu yaki da kansu, musamman masu alaka da TTP ko Jamaat-ul-Ahrar ko Lashkar-e-Islam, da kuma waɗanda ke da Baluchistan Liberation Army, wanda ya dauki alhakin yaki da sama a watan nan a yankin kudu na Sindh da kuma yankin tsakiya na Baluchistan Province.
Yawan jami'an sojojin Pakistan sun mutu a wannan watan a yankin Kudancin Baluchistan yayin yakin da 'yan ta'adda.
TTP ta dauki alhakin wani daga cikin mafi munin makamai a Pakistan a 2014, lokacin da makarantar sojojin Pakistan ta kashe kuma 140 suka mutu.
